ff the wedding,” he said. The Judge, Malam Salisu Abubakar-Tureta, ordered the court officials to have a look at the furniture bought by the defendant. Abubakar-Tureta adjourned the case until March 2. [NAN] Vanguard News Nigeria A 70-year-old man, Abdullahi Dahiru, on Thursday prayed a Shari’a court ll sitting at Magajin Gari, Kaduna to recover N25,000 dowry from Ms Rakiya Ibrahim, his former fiancée. October 24, 2019 In "News" A 32-year-old suitor Ahmad Sani, on Thursday prayed a Sharia Court in Magajin Gari in Kaduna State, to help him recover the N340,000 he allegedly paid as dowry to his would-be in-law. December 27, 2018 In "News" A 33-year-old man, Sabiu Umar, on Tuesday, prayed a Shari’a court sitting at Rigasa, Kaduna, to assist him recover N100,000 from his former fiancée’s father, Muhammad Sani. The complainant, a resident of Rigasa area, told the court that he had given the money to Sani as bride price and wedding… October 15, 2019 In "News"